  "local_port": 46914,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best book in preparation for bank exams?",
  "response": "Preparing for bank exams requires a focused approach and a good selection of study materials. Here are some of the best books recommended for various sections of bank exams in India:\n\n### General Awareness\n1. **\"Banking Awareness\" by Arihant Publications**\n   - Covers essential banking terms, policies, and current affairs related to the banking sector.\n   \n2. **\"Lucent's General Knowledge\" by Dr. Binay Karna and Manwendra Mukul**\n   - A comprehensive book for general knowledge, which is crucial for the general awareness section.\n\n### Quantitative Aptitude\n1. **\"Quantitative Aptitude for Competitive Examinations\" by R.S. Aggarwal**\n   - A must-have book covering a wide range of topics in quantitative aptitude with plenty of practice questions.\n\n2. **\"Fast Track Objective Arithmetic\" by Rajesh Verma**\n   - Great for quick revision and mastering shortcuts for solving arithmetic problems.\n\n### Reasoning Ability\n1. **\"A Modern Approach to Verbal & Non-Verbal Reasoning\" by R.S. Aggarwal**\n   - Comprehensive coverage of both verbal and non-verbal reasoning topics.\n\n2. **\"Analytical Reasoning\" by M.K. Pandey**\n   - Focuses on analytical reasoning, which is crucial for cracking the logical reasoning section.\n\n### English Language\n1. **\"Objective General English\" by S.P. Bakshi**\n   - Covers grammar, vocabulary, and comprehension, essential for the English section.\n\n2. **\"Word Power Made Easy\" by Norman Lewis**\n   - Excellent for building vocabulary and understanding word usage.\n\n### Computer Knowledge\n1. **\"Objective Computer Awareness\" by Arihant Publications**\n   - A good resource to understand basic computer concepts and terminology.\n\n### Special Mention for Overall Preparation\n1. **\"IBPS Bank PO/MT CWE - Common Written Examination\" by Disha Experts**\n   - A comprehensive guide tailored for IBPS PO exams, but useful for other bank exams as well.\n\n2. **\"Banking & Financial Awareness\" by Kiran Prakashan**\n   - Focuses specifically on banking and financial awareness, which is a critical component of many bank exams.\n\n### Practice Sets and Mock Tests\n1. **\"Bank PO Solved Papers\" by Arihant Publications**\n   - Contains previous years' question papers, which are essential for understanding the exam pattern and difficulty level.\n\n2. **\"Practice Sets for IBPS PO/MT\" by Disha Experts**\n   - Provides ample practice material in the format of the actual exam.\n\nRemember, while books are crucial, it's equally important to take mock tests and solve previous years' papers to understand the exam pattern and improve time management. Combine these resources with a structured study plan, and you'll be well-prepared for your bank exams.",
